A new name for an existing value does not automatically copy that value.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    names = {"Priya", "Grace"}
    same_names = names
]

`same_names` is another read-only view of the existing value.

This keeps ordinary code cheap. You can pass values around without copying
them first.

Shared access cannot be used to change the value. Mutation needs a mutable
binding and an explicit exclusive operation.
